</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,1127,2020]" pageId="7" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[201,262,1344,1367]" pageId="7" pageNumber="44">Male</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[276,340,1344,1367]" pageId="7" pageNumber="44">Head</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[355,477,1344,1368]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 12" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1268,1291]" captionTargetBox="[200,1365,176,1241]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,145,1247]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 12. Psilochlorops, head, dorsal and lateral view. 1, 7. Psilochlorops clavitibia (holotype). 2, 8. Psilochlorops brunneus (holotype), sp. n. 3, 9. Psilochlorops nigrifemur (holotype), sp. n. 4, 10. Psilochlorops paganelliae (holotype), sp. n. 5, 11. Psilochlorops elongatum (paratype), sp. n. 6, 12. Psilochlorops flavisoma (holotype), sp. n." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/214703/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="44">Figs. 5, 11</figureCitation>
). Head dark yellow, as wide as thorax, rather longer than broad in dorsal view, wider than high in lateral view; frontal triangle brown, margins at most gently curved, reaching anterior margin of frons; occiput with fine setulae; gena very short, postgena about 
<number box="[809,858,1416,1440]" pageId="7" pageNumber="44" value="0.65">0.65</number>
of eye height; eye rounded, long axis almost vertical; clypeus yellow; labella yellow, reduced; palpus yellow. First flagellomere dark yellow, with a pale brown area at apex; arista light brown; one row of interfrontals external to frontal triangle; postocellars convergent; outer vertical bristle well–developed (inner vertical cannot be seen in the only known specimen); one row of setulae at lower margin of gena, vibrissa thin. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[483,572,1560,1584]" pageId="7" pageNumber="44">Thorax</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[586,679,1560,1584]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 18" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1947,1970]" captionTargetBox="[197,1394,607,1885]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,574,1926]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 18. Psilochlorops, mesonotum, dorsal view. 13. Psilochlorops clavitibia (holotype). 14. Psilochlorops brunneus (holotype), sp. n. 15. Psilochlorops nigrifemur (holotype), sp. n. 16. Psilochlorops paganelliae (holotype), sp. n. 17. Psilochlorops elongatum (paratype), sp. n. 18. Psilochlorops flavisoma (paratype), sp. n." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/214704/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="44">Figs. 17</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[690,722,1560,1584]" captionStart="FIGURES 28 – 30" captionStartId="8.[151,264,940,963]" captionTargetBox="[176,1397,194,939]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1436,159,961]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 28 – 30. Psilochlorops elongatum (holotype), sp. n. 28. Habitus. 29. Hypandrial complex, ventral view. 30. Epandrium, ventral view. Legends, ep epandrium; hyp hypandrium; mes mesolobus; sur surstylus. Scale bar, 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/214708/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="44">28</figureCitation>
). Scutum twice longer than broad, mostly yellow, with five dark brown stripes with dark pilosity; scutellum yellow. Pleura dark yellow, post–pronotum with a small brown mark and three bristles; a brownish marking on notopleuron. Halter dark entirely yellow. Legs dark yellow, hind tibia light browndistal half of tarsi dark brown; tibial organ light brown, elongated. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1036,1100,1668,1693]" pageId="7" pageNumber="44">Wing</emphasis>
. Hyaline. Costal sections one to four: 
<date box="[243,363,1704,1728]" pageId="7" pageNumber="44" value="1913-03-14" valueMax="1913-03-07" valueMin="1913-03-14">
<number box="[243,312,1704,1728]" pageId="7" pageNumber="44" value="13.5" valueMax="14.0" valueMin="13.0">13-14</number>
- 
<number box="[321,336,1704,1728]" pageId="7" pageNumber="44" value="7.0">7</number>
- 
<number box="[345,359,1704,1728]" pageId="7" pageNumber="44" value="3.0">3</number>
.
</date>
R 
<number box="[389,397,1719,1733]" pageId="7" pageNumber="44" value="2.0">2</number>
+ 
<number box="[407,414,1719,1733]" pageId="7" pageNumber="44" value="3.0">3</number>
and R 
<number box="[485,493,1719,1733]" pageId="7" pageNumber="44" value="4.0">4</number>
+ 
<number box="[503,510,1719,1733]" pageId="7" pageNumber="44" value="5.0">5</number>
slightly concave; R 
<number box="[733,741,1719,1733]" pageId="7" pageNumber="44" value="4.0">4</number>
+ 
<number box="[750,757,1719,1733]" pageId="7" pageNumber="44" value="5.0">5</number>
and M 
<number box="[835,841,1719,1733]" pageId="7" pageNumber="44" value="1.0">1</number>
+ 
<number box="[851,860,1719,1733]" pageId="7" pageNumber="44" value="2.0">2</number>
rather divergent; M 
<number box="[1087,1093,1719,1733]" pageId="7" pageNumber="44" value="1.0">1</number>
+ 
<number box="[1103,1112,1719,1733]" pageId="7" pageNumber="44" value="2.0">2</number>
apex curved downward; r-m and dm-cu paralell, distant each other 
<number box="[593,642,1743,1767]" pageId="7" pageNumber="44" value="2.15">2.15</number>
as long as dm-cu. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[864,981,1742,1767]" pageId="7" pageNumber="44">Abdomen</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[998,1082,1743,1767]" captionStart="FIGURES 28 – 30" captionStartId="8.[151,264,940,963]" captionTargetBox="[176,1397,194,939]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1436,159,961]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 28 – 30. Psilochlorops elongatum (holotype), sp. n. 28. Habitus. 29. Hypandrial complex, ventral view. 30. Epandrium, ventral view. Legends, ep epandrium; hyp hypandrium; mes mesolobus; sur surstylus. Scale bar, 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/214708/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="44">
Fig. 
<number box="[1053,1082,1743,1767]" pageId="7" pageNumber="44" value="28.0">28</number>
</figureCitation>
). Tergites and sternites brown, lighter in distal segments of abdomen. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[581,712,1778,1803]" pageId="7" pageNumber="44">Terminalia</emphasis>
. Epandrium with a short projection, surstylus hook-like, fused to epandrium; mesolobus rectangular (
<figureCitation box="[553,638,1815,1839]" captionStart="FIGURES 28 – 30" captionStartId="8.[151,264,940,963]" captionTargetBox="[176,1397,194,939]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1436,159,961]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 28 – 30. Psilochlorops elongatum (holotype), sp. n. 28. Habitus. 29. Hypandrial complex, ventral view. 30. Epandrium, ventral view. Legends, ep epandrium; hyp hypandrium; mes mesolobus; sur surstylus. Scale bar, 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/214708/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="44">
Fig. 
<number box="[606,638,1815,1839]" pageId="7" pageNumber="44" value="30.0">30</number>
</figureCitation>
). Hypandrium broad (
<figureCitation box="[884,969,1815,1839]" captionStart="FIGURES 28 – 30" captionStartId="8.[151,264,940,963]" captionTargetBox="[176,1397,194,939]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1436,159,961]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 28 – 30. Psilochlorops elongatum (holotype), sp. n. 28. Habitus. 29. Hypandrial complex, ventral view. 30. Epandrium, ventral view. Legends, ep epandrium; hyp hypandrium; mes mesolobus; sur surstylus. Scale bar, 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/214708/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="44">
Fig. 
<number box="[937,969,1815,1839]" pageId="7" pageNumber="44" value="29.0">29</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,1127,2020]" box="[201,420,1851,1875]" pageId="7" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[201,295,1851,1875]" pageId="7" pageNumber="44">Female.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="44" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,1127,2020]" pageId="7" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[201,337,1886,1911]" pageId="7" pageNumber="44">Comments.</emphasis>
The 
<collectionCode box="[396,489,1887,1911]" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/6yx0-3nm7" name="Museu de Zoologia da Universidade de Sao Paulo" pageId="7" pageNumber="44">MZUSP</collectionCode>
collection has a third specimen with a label with the same data as the 
<typeStatus box="[1290,1388,1887,1911]" pageId="7" pageNumber="44">holotype</typeStatus>
and 
<typeStatus box="[151,250,1924,1948]" pageId="7" pageNumber="44">paratype</typeStatus>
, but the abdomen in this specimen is missing. It is not possible to be sure about the gender of the specimen and we preferred not to include this specimen in the 
<typeStatus box="[749,797,1959,1983]" pageId="7" pageNumber="44">type</typeStatus>
–series—even though it looks conspecific with the 
<typeStatus pageId="7" pageNumber="44">holotype</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
